My hair wasn’t always weak, thin or dry. 

But it did get to a point where it was lifeless and after much research I found out it was due to lack of nutrients, vitamins, change of environment and water (as I had moved from India to US)

I eat healthy but can’t ever focus on eating just the right foods for my scalp. The only other alternative is to find products that provides nutrients 

And I did😍

These products absolutely changed my hair health.

Because they have DHT BLOCKER in them.

DHT is a hormone made from testosterone. For some people, it can attach to hair follicles and make them shrink. This causes hair to grow thinner, weaker, and slower, and can eventually lead to hair loss.

DHT blockers help by lowering DHT levels, stopping it from hurting your hair follicles, and creating a healthier scalp so hair can grow better.

Not all haircare products have DHT blockers because they’re not all made to target hair loss, only products specifically formulated to prevent thinning or promote regrowth include them.

And my products contain DHT blocker in them along with active ingredients such as caffeine, fenugreek, D-biotin, and Capixyl.

LCO = Liquid, Cream, Oil

L – Liquid (or Leave-In Conditioner
* Add moisture to the hair.
* Use water or a water-based leave-in conditioner.
* This opens the moisture door, especially when applied to freshly washed, damp hair.

C – Cream
* Add softness, define curls, and boost moisture.
* Use a lightweight cream or styling milk that contains hydrating ingredients
* AVOID heavy butters, they can just sit on top.

O – Oil
* Seal everything in.
* Use a light to lock in the moisture and cream without making the hair greasy or coated.
* Since low porosity hair repels moisture, this last layer is key for sealing without suffocating the strand.

✨Why LCO is Better for Low Porosity Hair:
* The cream helps hydrate and soften the cuticle.
* Then the oil seals it in, without blocking moisture from entering first (which can happen if oil goes on too early).
* It mimics the way low porosity hair prefers layering, hydration first, seal last.

✨✨When to Use the LCO Method:
* After washing and conditioning
* During weekly or bi-weekly moisturizing sessions
* When prepping for protective styles or twist-outs
